# synth_macrosynth.m8script — T4 coverage for the Braids MacroSynth port,
# authored through the real UI edit path (M8_APP_AUTOMATION_SPEC.md Tier 4).
# MacroSynth is the one new synth type the UI actually supports: TYPE is
# hard-clamped to [SAMPLER, MACROSYN] (InstrumentScreen.cpp:209), and only
# InstrumentSamplerLayout.h/InstrumentMacrosynLayout.h exist. HyperSynth/
# FMSynth/WavSynth have no UI type selector or layout at all, and the Table
# screen has no edit mode wired up -- those get fixture-based coverage
# instead (load a pre-built .m8s, render, assert audio only) in the other
# synth_*.m8script / tables.m8script files.
#
# EDITING IDIOM (discovered 2026-07-17, differs from edit.m8script/
# save_reload.m8script's note-column pattern): a field on this screen is
# edited by `PushParam` inside `if (editHeld && arrow)` in
# InstrumentScreen.cpp -- editHeld is only true between X's own down/up
# events. A *sequential* `key X` / `key <DIR>` / `key X` spans three
# separate frames, so X's up event (and editHeld=false) has already been
# processed before the direction key is even pushed -- the value never
# changes. The correct idiom is the *compound* key syntax `key X+<DIR>`,
# which pushes X-down, DIR-down, DIR-up, X-up all within ONE frame, so
# editHeld is still true when the direction key fires. For a multi-step
# change, `repeat N { key X+<DIR> }` (each iteration is one full, independent
# edit cycle). (`closed_loop_glitch.m8script`/`closed_loop_fix.m8script` use
# the old sequential idiom and currently pass for an unrelated reason -- see
# the Tier 4 notes in M8_APP_AUTOMATION_SPEC.md; not fixed here to keep this
# change scoped to new coverage.)

load songs/sunrise.m8s
wait 1
assert_no_error

# Precondition, not enforced: songs/sunrise.m8s already plays instrument 00
# at C-4 on phrase 00 row 0 (verified via dump_screen, not assumed). If this
# ever fails, the fixture changed and the render below may go silent.
goto PHRASE
assert_screen row 3 contains "C-4"

# Instrument 00: SAMPLER -> MACROSYN
goto INSTRUMENT
assert_field TYPE SAMPLER
key X+UP
assert_field TYPE MACROSYN

# SHAPE (UI-clamped to [0,3] in InstrumentScreen.cpp even though the Braids
# engine models 0x00-0x2B; still enough to prove the edit path works and
# audibly changes the output)
key DOWN
key DOWN
key DOWN
assert_field SHAPE 00CSAW
repeat 3 {
    key X+UP
}
assert_field SHAPE 03SQU

# TIMBRE (default 0x80, range 0-255)
key DOWN
assert_field TIMBRE 80
repeat 32 {
    key X+UP
}
assert_field TIMBRE A0

# COLOR (default 0x80, range 0-255)
key DOWN
assert_field COLOR 80
repeat 32 {
    key X+UP
}
assert_field COLOR A0

render 1 macro.wav
assert_wav macro.wav nonfinite == 0
assert_wav macro.wav clipped == 0
assert_wav macro.wav peak > 0.0
